        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-12T15:42:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I find this comment very confusing.  If a frame is restore_previous it won\u0027t be used again so why shouldn\u0027t we overwrite it?\n\nYes, this comment is confusing. It\u0027s saying we shouldn\u0027t overwrite a frame that is *not* restore_previous, but that is digging into the weeds a bit, and reduces clarity rather than improves it.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e If a frame is restore_previous it will not be use again, therefore we should not ever overwrite fRestoreFrame with a frame tagged as restore_previous.\n\nI don\u0027t think we should mention fRestoreFrame; the general process is that if fActiveFrame should not be overwritten, we copy it to fRestoreFrame. I\u0027ve written a new comment that I think is more clear. WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "b1c59059_eb5bddc1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 173,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 174,
